TY  - JOUR
AU  - Phalippou, Ludovic
AU  - Gottschalg, Oliver
T1  - The Performance of Private Equity Funds
PY  - 2009
Y1  - 2009/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhn014
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 22
IS  - 4
SP  - 1747
EP  - 1776
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - The performance of private equity funds as reported by industry associations and previous research is overstated. A large part of performance is driven by inflated accounting valuation of ongoing investments and we find a bias toward better performing funds in the data. We find an average net-of-fees fund performance of 3% per year below that of the S&amp;P 500. Adjusting for risk brings the underperformance to 6% per year. We estimate fees to be 6% per year. We discuss several misleading aspects of performance reporting and some side benefits as a first step toward an explanation.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhn014
ER  - 



