TY  - JOUR
AU  - Braun, Matías
AU  - Larrain, Borja
T1  - Do IPOs Affect the Prices of Other Stocks? Evidence from Emerging Markets
PY  - 2009
Y1  - 2009/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhn025
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 22
IS  - 4
SP  - 1505
EP  - 1544
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We show that the introduction of a large asset permanently affects the prices of existing assets in a market. Using data from 254 initial public offerings (IPOs) in 22 emerging markets, we find that portfolios that covary highly with the IPO experience a decline in prices relative to other portfolios during the month of the issue. The effects are stronger when the IPO is issued in a market that is less integrated internationally and when the IPO is bigger. This evidence is consistent with the idea that shocks to asset supply have a significant effect on asset prices.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhn025
ER  - 



